PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772565072
OL,3,C'Extraordinary dignity' of Sarah
OL,4,CEverard's family hailed five years
OL,5,Cafter death
OL,7,FIn a statement issued by the force,
OL,8,FMetropolitan Police Commissioner Sir
OL,9,FMark Rowley said: "Sarah Everard
OL,10,Fshould still be here.
OL,12,F"Five years have passed since her
OL,13,Fsenseless and devastating murder.
OL,15,F"What happened to her was a profound
OL,16,Fbetrayal: of her, of her family and
OL,17,Floved ones, and of every person who
OL,18,Fplaces their trust in policing."
OL,26,@qD@SOUtD@AOUwD@AOUzD@`O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772565072
OL,3,C'Extraordinary dignity' of Sarah
OL,4,CEverard's family hailed five years
OL,5,Cafter death
OL,7,FHe said the fact that she was killed
OL,8,Fby a serving police officer, Wayne
OL,9,FCouzens, was "as devastating today as
OL,10,Fit was in 2021".
OL,12,F"It was an unthinkable abuse of power
OL,13,Fand a total violation of the values
OL,14,Fthat the Met, and policing stands for.
OL,16,F"On the day I heard what he had done,
OL,17,FI felt devastated for the immense harm
OL,18,Fhis actions caused to the trust that
OL,19,Funderpins our relationship with the
OL,20,Fcommunities we serve.
OL,26,@qD@NOUrD@OO]tD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1772565072
OL,3,C'Extraordinary dignity' of Sarah
OL,4,CEverard's family hailed five years
OL,5,Cafter death
OL,7,F"What he did shook policing to its
OL,8,Fcore. It made decent, dedicated
OL,9,Fofficers and staff across the country
OL,10,Ffurious that one of our own could
OL,11,Fcommit such a monstrous crime.
OL,13,F"We will always be deeply sorry: for
OL,14,Fthe unimaginable harm done to Sarah,
OL,15,Ffor the trauma endured by her family `
OL,16,Fwho have shown extraordinary dignity
OL,17,Fin the face of unbearable grief ` and
OL,18,Ffor the profound damage inflicted on
OL,19,Fthe trust Londoners should be able to
OL,20,Fplace in their police service."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOU|D@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/15
